column1: # This posture-analysis HMM model was built from annotations of 431 individuals observed in four separate experiments
# involving both live and UV-inactivated bacteria.
# All animals were QZO (N2-derived) wild-type grown at 20C
# and then transferred on their second day of adulthood at 32C
# State transitions are made requiring synchronous movement cessation and expansion with static transition probabilities.
# The following quantitative metrics are used to classify states:
#	Change in total intensity around the worm
